  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Cholera Prevention and Treatment in Leogane through Save the Children</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="3">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Cholera affected populations</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The global Red Cross network is coordinating an aggressive response to the cholera outbreak that spread throughout Haiti and into areas of the Dominican Republic. As part of this response, the American Red Cross partnered with a number of humanitarian organizations including Save the Children. Through this partnership, Save the Children set up two Cholera Treatment Units and eleven Oral Rehydration Points in rural areas of Leogane, and reached 45,494 people with health and hygiene promotion activities. The project also distributed relief supplies such as soap and aquatabs to 7,230 families.</narrative>
  </description>
